Services

Meet with a librarian

Learn to effectively search databases and optimize search strategies.

Request online meeting

Literature search

Request literature searches on health-related topics to support research projects and publications.

Request search

Interlibrary Loan and Digital Delivery

Request delivery of materials not currently available from the University of Minnesota Libraries, and digital copies of articles and book chapters from our print and microform collections.

Place a request

Researcher support

Find information, tools, and support for research projects including grant funding, data management, information discovery and management, scholarly identity and impact, copyright management and publishing.

Request online consultation

Systematic review

Collaborate with librarians to conduct systematic reviews of the literature.

Request review

Policy and news media impact

Request reports on individual or departmental research mentioned or cited in public policy, news media, blog posts, and other informational sites to broadly demonstrate research impact.

Request report

Course and instructor support

Work with your librarian to receive in-class instruction, individualized consultations for research projects, customized resource pages for courses, and guidance on resources for facilitating active learning.

Request online support

Course reserves

Request readings and other course materials for access by students in Canvas.

Place reserves

Peer tutoring

Vet Peer Assisted Coaching (VetPAC) is available in the Veterinary Medical Library.
